{
  "texts": [
    "We limited the data to humans and compared the no incentive condition to each one of the incentive conditions and averaged the bayes factor produced in each analysis.",
    "We further repeated this comparison for each outcome and took the average bayes factor of all analysis (see full model in SM).",
    "Overall, the average Bayes factor of the difference between incentive conditions and the non-incentive condition was 0.02 (inverse BF = 50).",
    "Put differently, we have evidence in our sample that it is 50 times more likely that incentives did not contribute to a significant improvement in reappraisal quality among humans across the four dimensions.",
    "Altogether, these results suggest strong evidence (Andraszewicz et al., n.d.) for the null effect."
  ]
}